Sentencas: The composite cathodes of La0.4Ce0.6O1.8 (LDC)-La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 (LSM)-8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) with different LDC contents were investigated for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with thin film YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: La0.4Ce0.6O1.8-La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia composite cathode for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxygen temperature-programmed desorption profiles of the LDC-LSM-YSZ composites indicate that the addition of LDC increases surface oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: La0.4Ce0.6O1.8-La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia composite cathode for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell performance was improved largely after the addition of LDC, and the best cell performance was achieved on the cells with the composite cathodes containing 10 wt% or 15 wt% LDC.
Titulo: La0.4Ce0.6O1.8-La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia composite cathode for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode polarization resistance was reduced significantly after the addition of LDC.
Titulo: La0.4Ce0.6O1.8-La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia composite cathode for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C and 650 degrees C, the polarization resistances of the cell with a 10 wt% LDC composite cathode are 70% and 40% of those of the cell with a LSM-YSZ composite cathode, respectively.
Titulo: La0.4Ce0.6O1.8-La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia composite cathode for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The impedance spectra show that the processes associated with the dissociative adsorption of oxygen and diffusion of oxygen intermediates and/or oxygen ions on LSM surface and transfer of oxygen species at triple phase boundaries are accelerated after the addition of LDC.
Titulo: La0.4Ce0.6O1.8-La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia composite cathode for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells
